Class PropertySetPanel

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.Component
      • java.awt.Container

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible
    public class PropertySetPanel
extends javax.swing.JPanel
    A container for GroupPanel instances used to display the properties and values available in a PropertySet.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • expandGroup

        public void expandGroup​(java.lang.String groupName)
        Expands the GroupPanel for the given group name, if one is present. This method behaves as if the user had expanded the group by using it's expansion icon.

        Note: All expansions will be performed on the Swing event dispatch thread.

        Parameters:
        groupName - a String containing the name of the panel to expand.

      • expandGroup

        public void expandGroup​(java.lang.String groupName,
                        boolean scrollToVisible)
        Expands the GroupPanel for the given group name, if one is present. This method behaves as if the user had expanded the group by using it's expansion icon.

        Note: All expansions will be performed on the Swing event dispatch thread.

        Parameters:
        groupName - a String containing the name of the panel to expand.
        scrollToVisible - if true the panel will attempt to scroll until the group is visible

      • highlightProperty

        public void highlightProperty​(java.lang.String propertyName)
        Expands, scrolls to and temporarily highlights the display of the property with the given name.

        Note: All highlights will be performed on the Swing event dispatch thread.

        Parameters:
        propertyName - a String containing the name (not display name) of the property to highlight.

      • getHighlightedProperty

        public java.lang.String getHighlightedProperty()
        Returns the name of the property currently selected in this property set panel.
        Returns:
        a String containing the name of the highlighted property or null if no property is currently highlighted

      • getTargetClass

        public java.lang.Class getTargetClass​(java.lang.Object[] targets)
        Retrieves a reference to the Class common to the objects in the given array.
        Parameters:
        targets - an Object[] containing the objects for which to retrieve the common Class.
        Returns:
        the Class of all of the elements in targets or null if not all of the elements use the same Class, there are no elements, or at least one element is null.

      • stopEditing

        public boolean stopEditing()
        Completes and stops the editing process by calling stopEditing on the currently focused PropertyPanel.
        Returns:
        true if there is a currently focused property editor and it is stopped by this method; false otherwise.

      • setTarget

        public void setTarget​(java.lang.Object[] targets,
                      AbstractComponent[] targetComponents)
        Set the panel to represent the properties that are common to the given target beans.
        Parameters:
        targetComponents - an AbstractComponent[] containing the component or components that are the owners of the given beans

      • setFocusSupportEnabled

        public void setFocusSupportEnabled​(boolean enabled)
        Enables or disables the Tab/Enter focus traversal behavior in this property set panel.

        Note that enabling this behavior for multiple property set panels will cause conflicts which cause both panels to discard focus.
